cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Behavioral Grounding Framework (BGF)"
abstract: >
  BGF is an open-source multi-agent economic simulation framework that grounds
  LLM-based agents in empirical sociodemographic microdata from the European
  Social Survey (ESS Round 11). It formalises an RLHF Cooperative Bias Index
  (B_RLHF) and a Behavioral Realism Metric (BRM), and supplies a deterministic
  rule-based ESS policy that reproduces Eurostat-range Gini and a perfect
  cross-cultural cooperation gradient against three independent benchmarks
  (ESS-11, WVS Wave 7, Herrmann-Thoeni-Gaechter 2008 PGG). The within-Mistral-7B
  grounded vs ungrounded contrast is a null result under the pre-registered
  10-seed N=100 confirmatory extension. At N=500 (T=30 complete, 2026-06-05),
  a self-amplifying RLHF cooperation cascade drives both conditions to 94-96%
  cooperation with B_RLHF 0.607/0.627 at terminal (2.6-2.8x the N=100 baseline);
  multi-seed confirmation (2 seeds/arm T=15, 2026-06-07): condA 89.7+/-1.3 pp vs
  condB 89.8+/-2.5 pp at R15 - cross-condition gap +0.1 pp (null, H2 consistent).
  Memory ablation H8 (24/24 cells) is falsified for both arms: full hierarchical
  memory suppresses rather than amplifies cooperation under grounding. Ships with
  1,578 automated tests and one-command reproduction via scripts/reproduce_paper.sh.
